ll changes color to show whether it is solid (blue), liquid (green), or gas (orange) at that temperature, based on its melting and boiling points.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"What formulas does the molar mass calculator support?\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"dt\",null,{\"className\":\"font-medium text-foreground\",\"children\":\"What formulas does the molar mass calculator support?\"}],[\"$\",\"dd\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"The calculator handles simple formulas (H2O, NaCl), parentheses (Ca(OH)2), brackets ([Cu(NH3)4]SO4), nested groups (Mg3(PO4)2), hydrate notation (CuSO4·5H2O), and Unicode subscript digits.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"Can I export the periodic table data?\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"dt\",null,{\"className\":\"font-medium text-foreground\",\"children\":\"Can I export the periodic table data?\"}],[\"$\",\"dd\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Yes. Click the Export button to download element data as CSV (for spreadsheets), JSON (for developers), PDF (print-ready table with all selected properties), or PNG (screenshot of the current table view). You can choose which properties to include.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"Does the electron configuration builder follow the Aufbau principle?\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"dt\",null,{\"className\":\"font-medium text-foreground\",\"children\":\"Does the electron configuration builder follow the Aufbau principle?\"}],[\"$\",\"dd\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Yes. The builder fills orbitals in the standard Aufbau order (1s → 2s → 2p → 3s → ...) and displays electrons following Hund's rule (maximum spin multiplicity). You can also click individual orbital boxes to create custom configurations.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"Does the tool work on mobile?\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"dt\",null,{\"className\":\"font-medium text-foreground\",\"children\":\"Does the tool work on mobile?\"}],[\"$\",\"dd\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"The periodic table is optimized for desktop viewports (1024px+) where you can see the full 18-column layout. It is usable on tablets in landscape mode. On phones, horizontal scrolling is available but the experience is best on larger screens.\"}]]}],\"$L2f\",\"$L30\",\"$L31\"]}]]}]\n24:null\n25:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Confusing atomic number with atomic mass\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Atomic number = proton count (unique to each element); atomic mass = average mass of isotopes (varies by sample). The table shows both — read the right one for your problem.\"}]]}]\n26:[\"$\",\"li\",\"Reading electron configuration left-to-right\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$1f:1:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Reading electron configuration left-to-right\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Electron configurations follow the Aufbau order (1s → 2s → 2p → 3s → 3p → 4s → 3d…), not strict atomic-number order. The viewer shows the proper filling order so you don't have to memorize the diagram.\"}]]}]]}]\n27:[\"$\",\"li\",\"Skipping isotope notation\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"iconNode\":\"$1f:1:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"chil